\c 1
\s1 ALLAH memanggil Yunus, tetapi dia melarikan diri
\p
\v 1 Pada suatu hari ALLAH berkata kepada Nabi Yunus, anak Amitai,
\p
\v 2 Aku telah melihat kejahatan penduduk Niniwe, kota yang besar itu. Pergi dan peringatkanlah kepada mereka bahwa Aku akan menghukum mereka karena kejahatan mereka.   Rima: harus pakai tanda kutip. Minta Paula untuk tunjukkan cara masukkan. Ini bukan " di keyboard. Bandingkan:  “I have \add seen\add* how wicked \add the people of\add* [MTY] the great city/Nineveh are. Therefore go there and warnthe people that \add I am planning to\add* destroy their city \add because of theirsins\add*.”
\v 3 Tetapi Yunus malah melarikan diri jauh dari hadapan ALLAH. Yunus pergi ke Yopa, tempat yang berlawanan dengan perintah Tuhan, di sana dia mendapat kapal,lalu membayarnya dan naik kapal itu menuju ke kota Tarsis.
\p
\v 4 Di dalam kapal, Yunus turun ke dek yang paling bawah, membaringkan diri di situ dan tertidur pulas.   ALLAH mengirimkan angin kencang ke laut lalu terjadilah badai besar yang dahsyat sehingga kapal itu terancam (terbelah / hancur).
\v 5 Karena itu, anak buah kapal menjadi takut dan setiap orang berdoa kepada allahnya untuk minta pertolongan. Mereka membuang barang-barang ke laut untuk meringankan beban kapal itu supaya tidak tenggelam.
\p
\v 6 Pada waktu kapten kapal turun ke dek yang paling bawah, lalu ia melihat Yunus di situ sedang tidur. lalu  terlelap. Lalu kapten kapal mendekati dan berkata kepada Yunus: " Bagaimana mungkin kamu bisa tidur terlelap dalam keadaan begini? Bangunlah, berdoalah kepada allahmu mungkin allahmu itu mau mengasihani dan menyelamatkan kita dari badai besar ini." Rima: Ubah tanda kutip menjadi seperti:  Then the captain went \add down\add* to where Jonah was sleeping soundly.\add He awoke him\add* and said \add to him\add*, “◄How can you sleep\add during a storm like this\add*?/You should not be sleeping \add during a storm likethis\add*!► [RHQ] Get up and pray to your god! Perhaps he will pity us and save us, in order that we will not drown!”\add But Jonah refused to do that\add*.
\p
\v 7 Setelah nakhoda kapal dan Yunus naik ke dek atas di kapal itu, para awak kapal berkata seorang kepada yang lain, "Mari kita cari tahu dengan cara buang undi supaya kita mengetahui siapa penyebab bencana ini terjadi atas kita." lalu mereka membuang undi dan Yunus yang kena undi.   [Rima: Banyak pembaca tidak akan tahu arti membuang undi. Saya lupa apa yang kita pakai dalam Matius 23, Mrk 15. Coba lihat apa yang TSI pakai.]
\v 8 Para awak kapal berkata kepada Yunus, "Apakah betul kamu penyebab bencana ini terjadi? Kamu berasal dari mana? Bangsa apa? 
\p
\v 9 Jonah replied, “I am a Hebrew. I worship Yahweh God, who \add livesin\add* heaven. He is the one who made the sea and the land. I am trying to escape from\add doing what\add* Yahweh \add told me to do\add*.”
\p
\v 10 After the sailors heard that, they were terrified. So they asked him, “Do you realize what\add trouble\add* you have caused?”
\p
\v 11 The \add storm kept getting worse and\add* the waves kept getting bigger. So\add one of\add* the sailors asked Jonah, “What should we do in order to make the sea become calm?”
\v 12 He replied, “Pick me up and throw me into the sea. \add If you dothat\add*, it will become calm. I know that this terrible storm is the result of my\add not doing what Yahweh told me to do\add*.”
\p
\v 13 But the sailors did \add not want to do that\add*. Instead, they tried hard to row the ship back to the land. But they could not do that, because the storm continued to get worse.
\v 14 Therefore they prayed to Yahweh, and \add one of them\add* prayed, “O Yahweh, please do not let us drown because of our causing this man to die. O Yahweh, you have done what you wanted to do.\add We do not know\add* \add if this man has sinned. If\add* he has not sinned, do not consider that we are guilty of sinning when we cause him to die!”
\v 15 Then they picked Jonah up and threw him into the sea. Then the sea became calm.
\v 16 \add When that happened\add*, the sailors became greatly awed at Yahweh's\add power\add*. So they offered a sacrifice to Yahweh, and they strongly promised\add him that they would do things that would please him\add*.
\p
\v 17 \add While they were doing that\add*, Yahweh sent a huge fish that swallowed Jonah. Then Jonah was inside the fish for three days and three nights.


